info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued October 30 at 11:19PM EDT until October 31 at 5:00AM EDT by NWS Key West
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM EDT TUESDAY... * WHAT...Saltwater flooding. * WHERE...Florida Keys. * WHEN...Until 5 AM EDT Tuesday, especially during the high tides. * IMPACTS...Saltwater flooding of low elevation streets and lots is expected. Some storm drains will overflow, and some seawalls and docks will be overtopped. Boaters can expect less clearance under fixed bridges. Motorists should remember that persistent puddles around the times of high tide are almost certain to contain a mix of saltwater.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
